<br>
From what i've seen, pickup groups are in the 55-56+ range mostly though (exceptions like clerics as usual can group earlier, etc).  If you solo &amp; want to keep doing that, dont bother with pop, its not for you.<br>
<br>
If you group &amp; plan on getting 3-4 more levels quickly anyways, i'd buy it, otherwise i'd pass unless you like to travel a lot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphyr>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 657<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/02 7:27:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Worth buying PoP at 52?</span><hr size=1> At 52 you get the following from PoP :<br>
<br>
1)Fast travel<br>
2)Some fairly easy quests that produce level 2 focus items (good for equiping your low level alts)<br>
3)A couple new spells : Tiny Companion (pet shrink), Refresh Summoning (level 44 pet heal), and in 2 levels Elemental Cloak (level 54 upgrade to Elemental Armor - mostly worthless due to stacking issues).<br>
4)Access to the new /raidwindow functionality<br>
<br>
In a few levels you will start to have a small chance of getting into pickup groups in the Tier 1 planes. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
